cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SI 

The paper deals with hyperspectral image restoration, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves capturing non-local similarity and spectral correlation using tensors, which is a technique commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the analytical solution for the proposed model, which falls under mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with low-level vision tasks such as denoising, deblurring, and super-resolution, which are topics related to signal processing and image analysis (cs.SI).
